1
00:00:07,532 --> 00:00:08,593
<b>I believe...</b>

2
00:00:10,632 --> 00:00:12,302
<b>there is a reason...</b>

3
00:00:13,233 --> 00:00:15,472
<b>to why someone survives.</b>

4
00:00:17,672 --> 00:00:20,312
<b>It's because there's something in this world only you can do.</b>

5
00:00:26,413 --> 00:00:27,952
<b>That's why the reason you're alive...</b>

6
00:00:29,853 --> 00:00:31,753
<b>may be a blessing to us.</b>

7
00:00:33,523 --> 00:00:36,393
<b>So Ji Su, you can do anything you want.</b>

8
00:00:38,862 --> 00:00:42,063
<b>You can rest, you can cry,</b>

9
00:00:43,662 --> 00:00:44,832
<b>and if it's too much,</b>

10
00:00:46,133 --> 00:00:48,302
<b>you don't have to try so hard to bear it.</b>

11
00:00:51,643 --> 00:00:53,342
<b>I'll be by your side.</b>

12
00:01:06,553 --> 00:01:08,122
<b>Why would you be by my side?</b>

13
00:01:09,523 --> 00:01:10,792
<b>I'll be in my place,</b>

14
00:01:11,922 --> 00:01:13,762
<b>and you'll be in yours.</b>

15
00:01:14,262 --> 00:01:15,333
<b>Okay.</b>

16
00:01:17,532 --> 00:01:19,032
<b>Anyone can see that this isn't right,</b>

17
00:01:20,872 --> 00:01:22,633
<b>and even if it's your first love,</b>

18
00:01:24,172 --> 00:01:26,672
<b>you can't justify something that's inappropriate.</b>

19
00:01:26,672 --> 00:01:27,842
<b>But why can't I...</b>

20
00:01:29,713 --> 00:01:31,542
<b>turn away from you?</b>

21
00:01:34,183 --> 00:01:36,213
<b>Why can't I just keep you in my memories?</b>

22
00:01:39,622 --> 00:01:41,053
<b>I kept thinking about it,</b>

23
00:01:43,993 --> 00:01:45,823
<b>and the answer was in our past.</b>

24
00:01:49,292 --> 00:01:50,463
<b>You told me...</b>

25
00:01:51,933 --> 00:01:53,062
<b>that I am...</b>

26
00:01:55,833 --> 00:01:57,243
<b>your belief and your world.</b>

27
00:02:04,083 --> 00:02:06,243
<b>There's something I couldn't say back to you.</b>

28
00:02:11,122 --> 00:02:13,023
<b>To me, you were my dream.</b>

29
00:02:18,923 --> 00:02:21,393
<b>I'm facing the dream I had lost,</b>

30
00:02:26,602 --> 00:02:27,833
<b>so I can't leave it...</b>

31
00:02:31,502 --> 00:02:33,072
<b>nor run away from it.</b>

32
00:02:39,143 --> 00:02:40,453
<b>Because that's my dream.</b>

33
00:02:55,532 --> 00:02:56,803
<b>Because it's a dream,</b>

34
00:03:04,203 --> 00:03:05,673
<b>we'll wake from it soon.</b>

35
00:03:52,782 --> 00:03:54,453
<b>I should go now.</b>

36
00:04:32,163 --> 00:04:33,262
<b>Jae Hyun.</b>

37
00:04:34,192 --> 00:04:35,192
<b>Yes?</b>

38
00:04:38,233 --> 00:04:40,572
<b>Sorry to ruin the mood,</b>

39
00:04:42,072 --> 00:04:44,272
<b>but I'm so cold and hungry.</b>

40
00:05:03,022 --> 00:05:04,022
<b>Yoon Ji Su.</b>

41
00:05:04,622 --> 00:05:07,293
<b>Are you upset? Are you?</b>

42
00:05:08,093 --> 00:05:10,163
<b>I thought you were all grown up,</b>

43
00:05:10,163 --> 00:05:11,533
<b>but you're a baby.</b>

44
00:05:19,343 --> 00:05:20,872
<b>Are you upset?</b>

45
00:05:21,072 --> 00:05:22,413
<b>You're not, are you?</b>

46
00:05:22,473 --> 00:05:23,483
<b>Whatever.</b>

47
00:05:23,483 --> 00:05:25,113
<b>I'm sorry.</b>

48
00:05:28,613 --> 00:05:30,983
<b>Hey. You'll catch a cold.</b>

49
00:06:01,082 --> 00:06:02,312
<b>(Jungang Market)</b>

50
00:06:25,903 --> 00:06:26,973
<b>That's the one.</b>

51
00:07:00,913 --> 00:07:02,072
<b>This is...</b>

52
00:07:02,913 --> 00:07:04,043
<b>clotted blood?</b>

53
00:07:05,012 --> 00:07:06,043
<b>Yes.</b>

54
00:07:06,983 --> 00:07:08,683
<b>When we have nosebleeds,</b>

55
00:07:08,683 --> 00:07:10,582
<b>the blob we feel...</b>

56
00:07:11,822 --> 00:07:13,053
<b>is this blood clot?</b>

57
00:07:15,923 --> 00:07:18,122
<b>Humans are so cruel.</b>

58
00:07:18,392 --> 00:07:21,233
<b>We even take the blood from cows?</b>

59
00:07:28,502 --> 00:07:30,502
<b>You aren't eating? It's delicious.</b>

60
00:07:30,772 --> 00:07:31,803
<b>What?</b>

61
00:07:36,012 --> 00:07:37,413
<b>Do they sell this in Seoul too?</b>

62
00:07:39,582 --> 00:07:40,683
<b>I'll buy you some.</b>

63
00:07:43,252 --> 00:07:44,653
<b>It's amazing.</b>

64
00:07:51,562 --> 00:07:52,622
<b>Jae Hyun.</b>

65
00:07:56,163 --> 00:07:58,363
<b>Weren't we a little cute back then?</b>

66
00:08:02,033 --> 00:08:03,072
<b>No.</b>

67
00:08:04,673 --> 00:08:06,473
<b>We were very cute.</b>

68
00:08:20,952 --> 00:08:24,892
<b>(When My Love Blooms)</b>

69
00:08:24,892 --> 00:08:26,962
<b>(Some topics were exaggerated for dramatic effect.)</b>

70
00:08:31,663 --> 00:08:33,832
<b>(Episode 5)</b>

71
00:08:37,942 --> 00:08:39,273
<b>Go on home.</b>

72
00:08:39,543 --> 00:08:40,612
<b>Ji Su.</b>

73
00:08:41,873 --> 00:08:44,242
<b>I said yesterday that I'd be by your side.</b>

74
00:08:44,712 --> 00:08:45,812
<b>I meant it.</b>

75
00:08:47,582 --> 00:08:48,883
<b>It was a dream.</b>

76
00:08:49,952 --> 00:08:51,553
<b>It's all a dream.</b>

77
00:08:52,383 --> 00:08:53,692
<b>I woke up.</b>

78
00:08:53,992 --> 00:08:56,452
<b>- So you should... - I'm not trying anything.</b>

79
00:08:57,393 --> 00:08:58,923
<b>I just want to stop you...</b>

80
00:08:59,893 --> 00:09:01,293
<b>from crying again.</b>

81
00:09:02,692 --> 00:09:04,303
<b>Don't worry.</b>

82
00:09:05,102 --> 00:09:08,332
<b>I cry in my dreams, but rarely in my real life.</b>

83
00:09:12,043 --> 00:09:13,373
<b>Don't you cry.</b>

84
00:09:13,373 --> 00:09:15,712
<b>If you do, I'll come for you.</b>

85
00:09:19,982 --> 00:09:22,653
<b>That sounded like a line from a Christmas carol.</b>

86
00:09:24,553 --> 00:09:25,653
<b>Get some rest.</b>

87
00:09:55,153 --> 00:09:56,312
<b>Where's my wife?</b>

88
00:09:56,553 --> 00:09:58,722
<b>Oh. She's not back yet.</b>

89
00:10:23,543 --> 00:10:25,543
<b>Hi. Come in.</b>

90
00:10:25,683 --> 00:10:28,013
<b>I have to leave soon. I'm shooting a movie.</b>

91
00:10:28,253 --> 00:10:29,383
<b>At what time?</b>

92
00:10:30,183 --> 00:10:31,283
<b>Around 3pm?</b>

93
00:10:32,352 --> 00:10:34,092
<b>Can you not do that?</b>

94
00:10:34,222 --> 00:10:36,293
<b>It bothers me that there are so many girls.</b>

95
00:10:36,322 --> 00:10:37,523
<b>They are nothing to me.</b>

96
00:10:37,523 --> 00:10:39,623
<b>I'll give you the money.</b>

97
00:10:39,663 --> 00:10:41,192
<b>I don't work for money.</b>

98
00:10:41,192 --> 00:10:42,192
<b>Then what for?</b>

99
00:10:42,192 --> 00:10:44,062
<b>Self-realization?</b>

100
00:10:45,503 --> 00:10:46,832
<b>You're not a teenager.</b>

101
00:10:49,303 --> 00:10:50,403
<b>See you another time.</b>

102
00:10:51,673 --> 00:10:52,942
<b>Wait.</b>

103
00:11:00,383 --> 00:11:02,212
<b>- Buy what you need. - It's fine.</b>

104
00:11:02,212 --> 00:11:03,553
<b>It's not fine.</b>

105
00:11:04,582 --> 00:11:06,153
<b>That bag is terrible.</b>

106
00:11:06,482 --> 00:11:07,523
<b>Throw it away.</b>

107
00:11:16,433 --> 00:11:17,533
<b>Yes, sir.</b>

108
00:11:17,763 --> 00:11:18,862
<b>Where are you?</b>

109
00:11:19,332 --> 00:11:20,362
<b>At home.</b>

110
00:11:20,732 --> 00:11:22,433
<b>Then come over.</b>

111
00:11:23,373 --> 00:11:25,242
<b>Okay. I will.</b>

112
00:11:30,582 --> 00:11:32,812
<b>Are you preparing for the parliamentary inspection?</b>

113
00:11:33,413 --> 00:11:34,413
<b>Yes.</b>

114
00:11:34,952 --> 00:11:37,683
<b>I heard they're trying to figure out...</b>

115
00:11:38,082 --> 00:11:41,053
<b>whether to grill you or boil you.</b>

116
00:11:42,123 --> 00:11:43,352
<b>It's fine.</b>

117
00:11:43,862 --> 00:11:47,592
<b>Assemblymen live for the fun of yelling at others.</b>

118
00:11:47,933 --> 00:11:49,933
<b>Bow a little when you need to,</b>

119
00:11:50,062 --> 00:11:51,933
<b>and pretend you respect them...</b>

120
00:11:51,933 --> 00:11:53,232
<b>with a few sweet phrases.</b>

121
00:11:53,972 --> 00:11:55,003
<b>Do you understand?</b>

122
00:11:55,133 --> 00:11:56,373
<b>Yes.</b>

123
00:11:56,732 --> 00:11:58,702
<b>What's up with Seo Kyung now?</b>

124
00:12:00,102 --> 00:12:02,442
<b>I told you to sort it out. Didn't you already?</b>

125
00:12:06,543 --> 00:12:08,183
<b>You don't fear me, do you?</b>

126
00:12:10,352 --> 00:12:11,952
<b>I fear myself.</b>

127
00:12:13,183 --> 00:12:14,322
<b>I can't control myself...</b>

128
00:12:14,322 --> 00:12:16,793
<b>when it comes to my own daughter.</b>

129
00:12:19,663 --> 00:12:22,263
<b>If you make my girl cry,</b>

130
00:12:23,133 --> 00:12:25,062
<b>you'll have to leave this house.</b>

131
00:12:27,702 --> 00:12:30,303
<b>You'll have nothing but shorts on.</b>

132
00:12:31,273 --> 00:12:32,442
<b>Will you be okay with that?</b>

133
00:12:43,553 --> 00:12:44,582
<b>Hey.</b>

134
00:12:44,582 --> 00:12:46,053
<b>- Sir? - Yes?</b>

135
00:12:46,283 --> 00:12:48,492
<b>Someone is using your wife's credit card...</b>

136
00:12:48,492 --> 00:12:52,023
<b>to spend thousands of dollars every few minutes.</b>

137
00:12:52,592 --> 00:12:53,692
<b>Where?</b>

138
00:12:54,492 --> 00:12:56,732
<b>At luxury label stores at the department store.</b>

139
00:13:01,472 --> 00:13:02,933
<b>How dare you come here?</b>

140
00:13:06,673 --> 00:13:08,043
<b>I thought you wanted me here.</b>

141
00:13:13,283 --> 00:13:15,153
<b>Were you with her?</b>

142
00:13:17,683 --> 00:13:20,822
<b>"I'm suffering. I'm pathetic."</b>

143
00:13:21,092 --> 00:13:23,992
<b>"Don't worry. I'll look after you."</b>

144
00:13:25,962 --> 00:13:28,033
<b>With a face full of pity,</b>

145
00:13:28,793 --> 00:13:31,803
<b>did you shoot your melodrama?</b>

146
00:13:34,773 --> 00:13:36,033
<b>You're drunk.</b>

147
00:13:44,442 --> 00:13:45,683
<b>You know what?</b>

148
00:13:46,513 --> 00:13:48,283
<b>I was with a man too.</b>

149
00:13:51,183 --> 00:13:54,123
<b>We're even.</b>

150
00:13:55,592 --> 00:13:57,423
<b>So don't be so serious.</b>

151
00:13:58,663 --> 00:14:01,832
<b>This is nothing at all.</b>

152
00:14:03,192 --> 00:14:08,033
<b>You and I both are way too stressed out.</b>

153
00:14:08,472 --> 00:14:10,133
<b>We need a diversion.</b>

154
00:14:13,972 --> 00:14:15,212
<b>It's nothing more,</b>

155
00:14:16,572 --> 00:14:18,082
<b>and nothing less.</b>

156
00:14:20,143 --> 00:14:21,212
<b>Right?</b>

157
00:15:20,773 --> 00:15:21,972
<b>Hello.</b>

158
00:15:22,712 --> 00:15:26,612
<b>I'm so sorry. I really loved your music.</b>

159
00:15:28,383 --> 00:15:29,683
<b>It can't be helped.</b>

160
00:15:30,413 --> 00:15:32,383
<b>I couldn't control my temper.</b>

161
00:15:32,783 --> 00:15:35,352
<b>It was great to see. I loved it.</b>

162
00:15:36,753 --> 00:15:41,462
<b>How much do you think I'll have to pay her back?</b>

163
00:15:41,962 --> 00:15:44,362
<b>- What? - The dress.</b>

164
00:15:44,562 --> 00:15:47,033
<b>I'll find out and get back to you.</b>

165
00:15:49,332 --> 00:15:52,273
<b>Will you work at another hotel?</b>

166
00:15:52,873 --> 00:15:55,072
<b>Tell me where so I can come along.</b>

167
00:15:56,673 --> 00:15:58,212
<b>I really don't know...</b>

168
00:15:59,112 --> 00:16:00,913
<b>where to go now.</b>

169
00:16:02,183 --> 00:16:03,352
<b>Cheer up.</b>

170
00:16:03,612 --> 00:16:05,423
<b>You work so hard.</b>

171
00:16:05,423 --> 00:16:07,592
<b>Your day will come soon.</b>

172
00:16:10,123 --> 00:16:13,592
<b>My good day hasn't come yet.</b>

173
00:16:14,933 --> 00:16:16,492
<b>I thought it would soon.</b>

174
00:17:02,013 --> 00:17:03,273
<b>Don't do it again.</b>

175
00:17:06,083 --> 00:17:07,242
<b>When around me,</b>

176
00:17:08,883 --> 00:17:10,923
<b>don't hold someone else's hand.</b>

177
00:17:14,123 --> 00:17:17,222
<b>You know why I'm like this.</b>

178
00:17:48,807 --> 00:17:51,118
<b>Even your fingernails are so weak.</b>

179
00:17:51,847 --> 00:17:53,317
<b>So why are you so mean?</b>

180
00:17:56,948 --> 00:17:58,918
<b>Do you think you're still fierce?</b>

181
00:18:03,997 --> 00:18:05,297
<b>You can't leave home.</b>

182
00:18:07,257 --> 00:18:08,728
<b>You told me to fight.</b>

183
00:18:09,468 --> 00:18:11,037
<b>Running away isn't fighting.</b>

184
00:18:11,267 --> 00:18:12,997
<b>I can't handle him.</b>

185
00:18:14,307 --> 00:18:15,368
<b>I'll come with you.</b>

186
00:18:15,837 --> 00:18:17,438
<b>You can't handle him either.</b>

187
00:18:17,807 --> 00:18:20,037
<b>Then what? We never see each other again?</b>

188
00:18:20,438 --> 00:18:23,847
<b>No. But I really think this isn't the right day.</b>

189
00:18:25,777 --> 00:18:28,388
<b>If it's not today, it's not tomorrow either.</b>

190
00:18:33,218 --> 00:18:34,757
<b>I want to ask you something.</b>

191
00:18:35,858 --> 00:18:38,597
<b>Why are you so harsh to Ji Su?</b>

192
00:18:39,057 --> 00:18:42,668
<b>Must I explain that to you?</b>

193
00:18:42,668 --> 00:18:45,337
<b>To be honest, I don't think I can accept...</b>

194
00:18:45,337 --> 00:18:46,898
<b>any explanation you give.</b>

195
00:18:50,007 --> 00:18:53,537
<b>Even if she's hit with a flower, I don't think I can take that.</b>

196
00:18:59,878 --> 00:19:02,747
<b>To be a warm-hearted prosecutor who helps the powerless outsiders.</b>

197
00:19:02,747 --> 00:19:05,118
<b>To be a fair prosecutor who only pursues the truth.</b>

198
00:19:05,118 --> 00:19:07,118
<b>To be a trustworthy prosecutor who wins trust and understanding.</b>

199
00:19:07,118 --> 00:19:09,128
<b>To be an upright prosecutor who is stricter to himself.</b>

200
00:19:09,757 --> 00:19:11,458
<b>You swore that oath,</b>

201
00:19:11,757 --> 00:19:14,527
<b>and out of all the prosecutors who also did,</b>

202
00:19:14,928 --> 00:19:17,067
<b>you reached the highest position.</b>

203
00:19:18,168 --> 00:19:19,368
<b>I ask you to...</b>

204
00:19:20,497 --> 00:19:22,537
<b>treat Ji Su with warmth.</b>

205
00:19:27,007 --> 00:19:28,378
<b>You're studying law?</b>

206
00:19:30,678 --> 00:19:31,718
<b>Yes.</b>

207
00:19:31,718 --> 00:19:33,378
<b>Will you take the law exam?</b>

208
00:19:35,448 --> 00:19:36,587
<b>I plan to.</b>

209
00:19:36,817 --> 00:19:38,718
<b>Is it because you're cautious,</b>

210
00:19:39,118 --> 00:19:41,428
<b>or because of your beliefs?</b>

211
00:19:49,997 --> 00:19:53,597
<b>You seem to lack both caution and beliefs.</b>

212
00:19:56,668 --> 00:19:57,878
<b>You should leave.</b>

213
00:19:58,408 --> 00:20:00,777
<b>I don't want to hear from or see you again.</b>

214
00:20:17,158 --> 00:20:19,257
<b>We're lucky that it ended at this.</b>

215
00:20:27,767 --> 00:20:28,767
<b>It's me.</b>

216
00:20:30,138 --> 00:20:32,108
<b>Find out about a kid for me.</b>

217
00:20:33,878 --> 00:20:36,148
<b>Law major, class of 1995, Han Jae Hyun.</b>

218
00:20:38,418 --> 00:20:40,378
<b>I think he's into protesting.</b>

219
00:20:41,188 --> 00:20:42,948
<b>Find out about his finances.</b>

220
00:20:44,287 --> 00:20:45,358
<b>Bye.</b>

221
00:20:53,158 --> 00:20:54,297
<b>Don't worry.</b>

222
00:20:56,198 --> 00:20:58,097
<b>I won't see him again.</b>

223
00:21:08,108 --> 00:21:11,448
<b>The dress costs 3,000 dollars.</b>

224
00:21:17,587 --> 00:21:19,618
<b>Did you practice a lot? Go on home then.</b>

225
00:21:19,618 --> 00:21:21,628
<b>- Goodbye. - Bye.</b>

226
00:21:28,728 --> 00:21:30,198
<b>Ma'am.</b>

227
00:21:31,638 --> 00:21:33,168
<b>Yes, go ahead.</b>

228
00:21:33,698 --> 00:21:34,767
<b>Well,</b>

229
00:21:36,567 --> 00:21:38,608
<b>do you know students who want private lessons?</b>

230
00:21:38,608 --> 00:21:42,047
<b>Ms. Yoon, don't you already teach a lot of private lessons?</b>

231
00:21:43,148 --> 00:21:44,448
<b>I am...</b>

232
00:21:45,017 --> 00:21:46,648
<b>in urgent need of money.</b>

233
00:21:46,747 --> 00:21:48,587
<b>I can sympathize with you,</b>

234
00:21:49,487 --> 00:21:52,388
<b>but it's not like I have a list of students for private lessons.</b>

235
00:21:53,188 --> 00:21:55,257
<b>Anyway, I'll tell you as soon as I get a request.</b>

236
00:21:55,858 --> 00:21:58,358
<b>Thank you. Thank you so much.</b>

237
00:22:11,178 --> 00:22:13,807
<b>(Part-time Paradise, waitress wanted, kitchen assistant wanted)</b>

238
00:22:19,448 --> 00:22:21,718
<b>(Looking for a part-timer at a pork rib restaurant)</b>

239
00:22:31,898 --> 00:22:34,297
<b>(Special Exhibition on Leslie Cheung)</b>

240
00:22:38,037 --> 00:22:40,767
<b>(Pork Ribs)</b>

241
00:22:55,118 --> 00:22:56,347
<b>So Ji Su,</b>

242
00:22:57,247 --> 00:22:58,358
<b>you can do anything you want.</b>

243
00:22:59,958 --> 00:23:01,188
<b>You can rest,</b>

244
00:23:02,027 --> 00:23:03,257
<b>you can cry,</b>

245
00:23:04,698 --> 00:23:05,928
<b>and if it's too much,</b>

246
00:23:06,228 --> 00:23:08,327
<b>you don't have to try so hard to bear it.</b>

247
00:23:11,837 --> 00:23:13,597
<b>I'll be by your side.</b>

248
00:23:33,718 --> 00:23:34,787
<b>Hey, Young Woo.</b>

249
00:23:34,787 --> 00:23:35,827
<b>Where are you?</b>

250
00:23:36,057 --> 00:23:37,458
<b>I'm home.</b>

251
00:23:37,858 --> 00:23:39,027
<b>What are you doing?</b>

252
00:23:39,198 --> 00:23:40,327
<b>I'm washing dishes.</b>

253
00:23:40,997 --> 00:23:42,428
<b>Where are you? Send me the address.</b>

254
00:23:43,228 --> 00:23:45,037
<b>If you don't, I'll report you missing to the police.</b>

255
00:23:48,208 --> 00:23:50,108
<b>If you want a job, work at my bar.</b>

256
00:23:50,307 --> 00:23:51,678
<b>Their hourly rate is high.</b>

257
00:23:51,678 --> 00:23:52,878
<b>I'll pay you the same rate.</b>

258
00:23:52,938 --> 00:23:54,678
<b>I know your bar is slow.</b>

259
00:23:55,047 --> 00:23:56,448
<b>You don't want to play the piano anymore?</b>

260
00:23:56,448 --> 00:23:57,918
<b>Can you do manual work with your hands?</b>

261
00:23:57,948 --> 00:23:59,817
<b>Rubber gloves are pretty sturdy these days.</b>

262
00:23:59,878 --> 00:24:01,718
<b>Why are you working at restaurants?</b>

263
00:24:03,188 --> 00:24:04,858
<b>I was doing a part-time gig at the hotel.</b>

264
00:24:05,658 --> 00:24:07,287
<b>And I ruined a brand designer's dress.</b>

265
00:24:07,958 --> 00:24:10,327
<b>Find another hotel to work at.</b>

266
00:24:10,928 --> 00:24:12,428
<b>- I don't want to. - Why not?</b>

267
00:24:13,757 --> 00:24:16,628
<b>I can't think while doing this physical labor. It's nice.</b>

268
00:24:16,827 --> 00:24:19,337
<b>Besides, it's pathetic that I'm trying to make money...</b>

269
00:24:19,337 --> 00:24:21,668
<b>at working at a hotel like I'm classy or something.</b>

270
00:24:22,037 --> 00:24:24,737
<b>I had to eat brunches with the other mothers at the hotel,</b>

271
00:24:24,878 --> 00:24:26,638
<b>so I wore a mask.</b>

272
00:24:26,638 --> 00:24:28,908
<b>My whole life had been appalling.</b>

273
00:24:31,118 --> 00:24:32,618
<b>Now, I'll live without a mask.</b>

274
00:24:35,918 --> 00:24:37,017
<b>Actually,</b>

275
00:24:37,718 --> 00:24:39,358
<b>I never got to tell you,</b>

276
00:24:40,787 --> 00:24:43,827
<b>but you look much better without a mask.</b>

277
00:24:44,458 --> 00:24:45,958
<b>Do you mean it? Or is that sarcasm?</b>

278
00:24:46,057 --> 00:24:47,527
<b>It's the truth.</b>

279
00:24:48,997 --> 00:24:51,468
<b>That's heartbreaking. I tried to look my best.</b>

280
00:24:52,097 --> 00:24:53,468
<b>Don't you have a mirror at home?</b>

281
00:24:54,537 --> 00:24:56,837
<b>My gosh, that's why you're still single.</b>

282
00:24:57,537 --> 00:24:59,108
<b>Hey, wait up.</b>

283
00:25:04,678 --> 00:25:07,648
<b>You must be busy. I'm sorry to ask you to come back.</b>

284
00:25:08,347 --> 00:25:10,587
<b>It's all right. What is this about?</b>

285
00:25:10,718 --> 00:25:11,787
<b>Well...</b>

286
00:25:23,497 --> 00:25:25,368
<b>We should settle up.</b>

287
00:25:26,237 --> 00:25:27,237
<b>Yes.</b>

288
00:25:27,398 --> 00:25:29,938
<b>"Since I'm rich, I don't want your money."</b>

289
00:25:30,408 --> 00:25:31,908
<b>I don't do that.</b>

290
00:25:32,208 --> 00:25:34,007
<b>I learned it since I was a kid...</b>

291
00:25:34,277 --> 00:25:36,077
<b>that things must be clear when it comes to money.</b>

292
00:25:36,277 --> 00:25:37,577
<b>I'll pay you in a week.</b>

293
00:25:37,577 --> 00:25:39,178
<b>Do you think you only have to pay for the dress?</b>

294
00:25:40,718 --> 00:25:44,047
<b>Why won't you compensate for trying to wreck my family?</b>

295
00:25:46,858 --> 00:25:49,128
<b>I already know what you and Jae Hyun will tell me.</b>

296
00:25:49,458 --> 00:25:51,698
<b>Since I cheated first, you think...</b>

297
00:25:51,958 --> 00:25:53,658
<b>I don't deserve to say anything.</b>

298
00:25:55,797 --> 00:25:57,628
<b>Then, you should've stopped where I stopped.</b>

299
00:26:00,638 --> 00:26:02,708
<b>Have fun with him for a while and leave him,</b>

300
00:26:04,168 --> 00:26:06,577
<b>so he doesn't have an ounce of sympathy...</b>

301
00:26:06,708 --> 00:26:08,478
<b>and lingering attachment for you.</b>

302
00:26:11,747 --> 00:26:14,448
<b>Then, I'll settle that you paid me...</b>

303
00:26:14,718 --> 00:26:16,218
<b>everything you owe me.</b>

304
00:26:19,918 --> 00:26:21,428
<b>For your information,</b>

305
00:26:21,658 --> 00:26:23,327
<b>I'm not ethical at all.</b>

306
00:26:24,827 --> 00:26:25,858
<b>Be it your hair or whatnot.</b>

307
00:26:25,858 --> 00:26:27,497
<b>I'll grab everything I can put my hands on.</b>

308
00:26:27,527 --> 00:26:29,497
<b>I'm very good at slapping people...</b>

309
00:26:29,728 --> 00:26:31,198
<b>and splashing water.</b>

310
00:26:54,928 --> 00:26:58,158
<b>We'll begin the audit for illegally terminating temporary workers...</b>

311
00:26:58,358 --> 00:26:59,928
<b>at Hyung Sung Group...</b>

312
00:26:59,928 --> 00:27:01,827
<b>and issued stocks under borrowed names.</b>

313
00:27:01,928 --> 00:27:04,297
<b>All the account holders who lent their names...</b>

314
00:27:04,468 --> 00:27:06,337
<b>stated that the real owner of their stocks...</b>

315
00:27:06,337 --> 00:27:08,868
<b>is you, Vice-President Han Jae Hyun.</b>

316
00:27:09,067 --> 00:27:11,438
<b>If we add up all the stocks, it calculates up to...</b>

317
00:27:11,438 --> 00:27:13,908
<b>35 percent of all the stocks...</b>

318
00:27:14,277 --> 00:27:18,077
<b>when the chairman, Jang San, owns only 21 percent of the stocks.</b>

319
00:27:18,777 --> 00:27:19,847
<b>The employees with the permanent positions...</b>

320
00:27:19,847 --> 00:27:22,148
<b>make up less than 60 percent of the company.</b>

321
00:27:23,087 --> 00:27:25,118
<b>Hyung Sung Group is a big company.</b>

322
00:27:25,317 --> 00:27:26,718
<b>Why would you do something like that?</b>

323
00:27:27,118 --> 00:27:30,128
<b>I will answer your question after looking into...</b>

324
00:27:30,128 --> 00:27:31,128
<b>that matter.</b>

325
00:27:31,128 --> 00:27:32,797
<b>What do you know then?</b>

326
00:27:33,027 --> 00:27:35,327
<b>If you don't know anything, why did you come?</b>

327
00:27:35,628 --> 00:27:37,198
<b>You should be ashamed of yourself.</b>

328
00:27:37,868 --> 00:27:38,997
<b>Besides,</b>

329
00:27:39,638 --> 00:27:42,037
<b>didn't you work hard campaigning when you were in college?</b>

330
00:27:43,337 --> 00:27:46,478
<b>That's not all. From what I know, you used to be in a labor movement.</b>

331
00:27:47,608 --> 00:27:49,448
<b>What a turncoat.</b>

332
00:27:54,378 --> 00:27:56,148
<b>You're not going to attend the festival?</b>

333
00:27:56,247 --> 00:27:57,247
<b>(May 1994)</b>

334
00:27:57,247 --> 00:27:58,257
<b>No.</b>

335
00:27:58,418 --> 00:28:00,718
<b>Why not? I really want to go.</b>

336
00:28:01,118 --> 00:28:02,327
<b>You should go.</b>

337
00:28:03,688 --> 00:28:06,398
<b>Everyone is attending the festival with their boyfriend or girlfriend.</b>

338
00:28:07,158 --> 00:28:08,928
<b>There's a strike for the subway union.</b>

339
00:28:08,928 --> 00:28:10,597
<b>And there's Uruguay Round,</b>

340
00:28:11,597 --> 00:28:14,067
<b>the school election, and a tuition protest.</b>

341
00:28:16,468 --> 00:28:17,837
<b>That was a lie.</b>

342
00:28:19,878 --> 00:28:21,277
<b>I'm really moody these days.</b>

343
00:28:21,807 --> 00:28:22,807
<b>What?</b>

344
00:28:23,148 --> 00:28:25,678
<b>I've been rebelling without a reason and feeling rebellious.</b>

345
00:28:26,418 --> 00:28:27,648
<b>I feel like...</b>

346
00:28:27,648 --> 00:28:29,888
<b>I've been copying the activists from the 80s...</b>

347
00:28:30,688 --> 00:28:33,087
<b>and playing politics like grown-ups, so I'm thinking about it.</b>

348
00:28:33,787 --> 00:28:34,987
<b>I have a lot on my mind,</b>

349
00:28:35,358 --> 00:28:37,458
<b>so I can't go to the festival and have fun.</b>

350
00:28:39,158 --> 00:28:41,868
<b>Jae Hyun, when will you enjoy your life?</b>

351
00:28:43,767 --> 00:28:45,737
<b>When the world is good?</b>

352
00:28:47,138 --> 00:28:49,368
<b>I hope the world becomes good in no time.</b>

353
00:28:50,267 --> 00:28:51,307
<b>Goodness.</b>

354
00:28:53,737 --> 00:28:56,077
<b>I have a meeting in the club room. You can come with me.</b>

355
00:28:58,478 --> 00:29:00,118
<b>100 liberal arts students.</b>

356
00:29:00,118 --> 00:29:01,247
<b>50 math and science students.</b>

357
00:29:01,247 --> 00:29:03,547
<b>40 law majors. And what about them?</b>

358
00:29:03,688 --> 00:29:04,718
<b>How many?</b>

359
00:29:04,787 --> 00:29:06,918
<b>I'll know once Kyung Ho comes.</b>

360
00:29:06,987 --> 00:29:08,787
<b>If we get 50 students from their side,</b>

361
00:29:08,787 --> 00:29:10,428
<b>we can gather 500 students.</b>

362
00:29:10,628 --> 00:29:11,898
<b>We'll pick out good runners...</b>

363
00:29:11,898 --> 00:29:14,257
<b>and put 40 students in the 1st and 2nd rows.</b>

364
00:29:14,358 --> 00:29:15,827
<b>Then, our form will be somewhat ready.</b>

365
00:29:15,868 --> 00:29:17,468
<b>We need way more than 500.</b>

366
00:29:17,468 --> 00:29:19,037
<b>It's getting worse every year.</b>

367
00:29:19,037 --> 00:29:22,307
<b>It makes me wonder if we should take softer approaches.</b>

368
00:29:22,708 --> 00:29:25,337
<b>"Revolution, purge, and destruction."</b>

369
00:29:26,178 --> 00:29:27,978
<b>Our terms can sound too aggressive.</b>

370
00:29:33,047 --> 00:29:34,247
<b>Hey.</b>

371
00:29:35,118 --> 00:29:37,047
<b>The students from my department can't join.</b>

372
00:29:37,047 --> 00:29:38,118
<b>Why not?</b>

373
00:29:38,388 --> 00:29:40,587
<b>They're giving a last-minute test to business majors.</b>

374
00:29:40,658 --> 00:29:43,057
<b>Come on. Tell them to die.</b>

375
00:29:43,158 --> 00:29:45,428
<b>How do they expect to join us when they're worried about tests?</b>

376
00:29:45,428 --> 00:29:47,398
<b>Well, this test will be reflected on their grades.</b>

377
00:29:47,398 --> 00:29:48,728
<b>We get grades too.</b>

378
00:29:48,728 --> 00:29:50,797
<b>Do you think I get Fs because I want to?</b>

379
00:29:50,797 --> 00:29:52,138
<b>You think I collect Fs?</b>

380
00:29:52,698 --> 00:29:55,037
<b>Seriously. The student council is a bigger problem.</b>

381
00:29:55,668 --> 00:29:57,567
<b>They study for TOEIC.</b>

382
00:29:58,178 --> 00:29:59,938
<b>Or they are dating.</b>

383
00:30:00,737 --> 00:30:01,807
<b>You know?</b>

384
00:30:02,208 --> 00:30:04,608
<b>We are definitely losing our momentum.</b>

385
00:30:04,608 --> 00:30:05,718
<b>It's because we have a civilian government.</b>

386
00:30:05,718 --> 00:30:06,878
<b>Didn't I tell you?</b>

387
00:30:06,878 --> 00:30:09,017
<b>Student campaigning is like a bicycle.</b>

388
00:30:09,148 --> 00:30:11,958
<b>We must keep campaigning without skipping a day.</b>

389
00:30:11,987 --> 00:30:14,188
<b>Endlessly. If we don't have momentum, what should we do?</b>

390
00:30:14,188 --> 00:30:15,228
<b>- We must... - Do you...</b>

391
00:30:16,358 --> 00:30:18,027
<b>just want to ride it?</b>

392
00:30:19,327 --> 00:30:21,428
<b>- What? - Where is the bicycle headed?</b>

393
00:30:23,728 --> 00:30:25,097
<b>What's its destination?</b>

394
00:30:25,698 --> 00:30:27,638
<b>Gosh, you punk.</b>

395
00:30:27,968 --> 00:30:31,507
<b>Because you have a calculative approach and a negative mindset,</b>

396
00:30:31,608 --> 00:30:33,737
<b>our organization is going down the drain.</b>

397
00:30:33,737 --> 00:30:35,277
<b>Since your grades are a mess,</b>

398
00:30:35,708 --> 00:30:38,118
<b>if you graduate with these grades, you won't ever get a job.</b>

399
00:30:38,317 --> 00:30:40,978
<b>So I know that you're trying to get a job in the political world.</b>

400
00:30:41,077 --> 00:30:42,718
<b>Some of us came here to make changes...</b>

401
00:30:42,718 --> 00:30:44,388
<b>in the world while ignoring our studies.</b>

402
00:30:44,858 --> 00:30:46,718
<b>Don't use us to push your bicycle.</b>

403
00:30:52,958 --> 00:30:56,097
<b>Especially, the Jangs of Hyung Sung Group...</b>

404
00:30:56,368 --> 00:30:57,997
<b>have been swindling profits...</b>

405
00:30:58,067 --> 00:30:59,597
<b>to satisfy their own interests...</b>

406
00:30:59,597 --> 00:31:01,368
<b>through countless ways such as...</b>

407
00:31:01,368 --> 00:31:03,837
<b>owning stocks under borrowed-names and creating a slush fund.</b>

408
00:31:04,168 --> 00:31:06,007
<b>However, they terminated...</b>

409
00:31:06,208 --> 00:31:07,737
<b>all of the temporary workers...</b>

410
00:31:08,108 --> 00:31:10,247
<b>and showed immoral conduct at the highest degree.</b>

411
00:31:12,777 --> 00:31:14,547
<b>- Tough day, sir. - Yes.</b>

412
00:31:15,918 --> 00:31:18,888
<b>The account holders must have stated truthfully.</b>

413
00:31:18,888 --> 00:31:21,057
<b>That the real owner of the stocks is me.</b>

414
00:31:21,858 --> 00:31:24,228
<b>They are in a hurry to transfer the title.</b>

415
00:31:24,327 --> 00:31:26,057
<b>I'm thinking about handing out number tickets.</b>

416
00:31:26,728 --> 00:31:29,168
<b>Once the titles are transferred, we'll have to pay taxes.</b>

417
00:31:29,797 --> 00:31:32,537
<b>Seoul Bank is still working on the paperwork.</b>

418
00:31:32,537 --> 00:31:33,737
<b>I've been on their tails.</b>

419
00:31:34,497 --> 00:31:37,608
<b>By the way, we can resolve the civil suit this way.</b>

420
00:31:37,807 --> 00:31:39,108
<b>What about the criminal suit?</b>

421
00:31:39,638 --> 00:31:41,547
<b>Should I meet with prosecutors in advance?</b>

422
00:31:41,547 --> 00:31:43,547
<b>- There's no need. - Why not?</b>

423
00:31:44,448 --> 00:31:46,118
<b>I already did.</b>

424
00:31:49,448 --> 00:31:51,658
<b>- Mr. Jung. - Yes, sir.</b>

425
00:31:52,888 --> 00:31:53,958
<b>How come no one knows...</b>

426
00:31:53,958 --> 00:31:55,628
<b>I negotiated with the terminated workers?</b>

427
00:31:56,327 --> 00:31:57,628
<b>Is the PR team slacking off?</b>

428
00:31:58,297 --> 00:31:59,928
<b>I'll check on it and handle it right away.</b>

429
00:32:01,868 --> 00:32:03,368
<b>I'm sure they all saw it.</b>

430
00:32:17,908 --> 00:32:19,948
<b>- Jun Woo. - Yes, sir.</b>

431
00:32:20,978 --> 00:32:23,747
<b>The black car behind us. How long has it been following us?</b>

432
00:32:24,517 --> 00:32:25,688
<b>I see. Well,</b>

433
00:32:26,487 --> 00:32:28,327
<b>I think it's been following us from the parking lot.</b>

434
00:32:28,858 --> 00:32:31,057
<b>- Since today? - No, it started a few days ago.</b>

435
00:32:44,018 --> 00:32:46,018
<b>- Jun Woo. - Yes, sir.</b>

436
00:32:46,989 --> 00:32:49,888
<b>The black car behind us. How long has it been following us?</b>

